channel.title: Daggett County|Utah|United States on Roadsign Pictures
channel.description: Recent content in Daggett County|Utah|United States on Roadsign Pictures

item.title: UT-43 West - Distance Marker
item.description: Distance marker on UT-43 west. Distance to Mountain View (WY), Evanston (WY), and Salt Lake City. Access to Salt Lake City via UT-43 west involves cutting through the southwest corner of Wyoming.

item.title: End UT-43 at Utah-Wyoming Line
item.description: End UT-43 at Utah-Wyoming State Line. UT-43 becomes WY-414 in Wyoming.

item.title: UT-43 - Welcome To Utah - Daggett County
item.description: Welcome To Utah / Daggett County on UT-43. The Wyoming milemarker is in the foreground.

item.title: UT-43 West at UT-44
item.description: UT-43 west at UT-44 in Manila. Use UT-43 west for Mountain View (Wyoming). Use UT-44 South for Vernal and Flaming Gorge Dam.

item.title: UT-43 West - Manila
item.description: Entering Manila on UT-43 west. Manila is the county seat of Daggett County Utah.

item.title: UT-43 West at UT-44
item.description: UT-43 west at UT-44 in Manila. Sinclair gasoline dinosaur in foreground of photo.

item.title: US-191 North - Distance Marker
item.description: Distance marker on US-191 north. Distance to Rock Springs (Wyoming). This is the last distance marker on US-191 north in Utah.

item.title: US-191 North - Winter Driving Information
item.description: Winter Driving information for US-191 north in Wyoming - 8 miles ahead.

item.title: US-191 North - Dutch John
item.description: US-191 North at Dutch John junction.

item.title: US-191 North - Flaming Gorge Dam
item.description: Flaming Gorge Dam on US-191 north. The Flaming Gorge Dam is on the Green River. Behind the dam is Flaming Gorge Reservoir which is part in Utah, and part in Wyoming.

item.title: US-191 North - Daggett County
item.description: US-191 north in Daggett County. Winter closure sign for US-191 in Wyoming - 17 miles ahead. The winter closure sign appears to have been placed by the Wyoming DOT.

item.title: US-191 North at UT-44
item.description: US-191 North (Flaming Gorge Uintas Scenic Byway) at UT-44 in Daggett County. Turn right to continue north on US-191.

item.title: US-191 North at UT-44
item.description: US-191 north at UT-44 junction in Daggett County. Turn right to continue on US-191 north to Dutch John and Rock Springs (Wyoming). Continue straight for UT-44 to Manila.

item.title: US-191 North Approaching UT-44
item.description: US-191 North approaching UT-44 in Daggett County.

item.title: US-191 North - Flaming Gorge National Recreation Area
item.description: Entering the Flaming Gorge National Recreation Area on US-191 north.

item.title: US-191 North - Daggett County
item.description: Entering Daggett County on US-191 North. Summit at Elevation 8428 Feet. Daggett County is the least populated county in Utah

item.title: Welcome To Utah - Browns Park
item.description: Welcome to Utah on CH-1364 (Browns Park Road). This welcome sign was posted by the Utah Division of Wildlife Resources. Continue west on Browns Park Road for US-191.

item.title: Utah State Line on CR-1364
item.description: Utah State Line on CR-1364 (Browns Park Road) at the Wyoming-Utah Border. There is a cattle guard marking the state line.

item.title: US-191 North
item.description: US-191 north just north of UT-44. Folded up sign to the right is a winter road warning for the Wyoming stretch of US-191.

item.title: End UT-44 East at US-191
item.description: End UT-44 east at US-191.

item.title: UT-44 East Approaching US-191
item.description: UT-44 east approaching US-191. Use US-191 north for Flaming Gorge Dam, Dutch John, and Rock Springs (Wyoming).

item.title: Welcome To Utah on UT-43 West
item.description: Welcome to Utah on UT-43 West. The new Utah welcome signs have a different logo for each region of the State. The logo in this region is a Dinosaur. Taken at the Utah-Wyoming State Line.

item.title: UT-43 East at UT-44
item.description: UT-43 east at UT-44

item.title: UT-43 East Approaching UT-44
item.description: UT-43 east approaching UT-44. Use UT-44 east for Vernal, Dutch John, and Flaming Gorge Dam. Continue east on UT-43 for Green River.

item.title: UT-43 East Approaching UT-44
item.description: UT-43 east approaching UT-44. UT-44 is a Utah Scenic Byway.

item.title: End UT-44 North at UT-43
item.description: End UT-44 north at UT-43 to Salt Lake and Green River, in Manila.

item.title: End UT44 North at UT-43
item.description: End of UT-44 at UT-43 in Manilla.

item.title: Jct. UT-44 on UT-43 West
item.description: UT-43 west approaching UT-44 in Manilla. UT-44 combined with US-191 is the Utah portion of the Flaming Gorge Loop.

item.title: US-191 North at UT-44
item.description: US-191 north at UT-44 junction in Daggett County, on the southern end of Flaming Gorge NRA.

item.title: UT-43 West at UT-44
item.description: UT-43 west at UT-44 junction in Manilla.

item.title: UT-43 West at UT-44
item.description: UT-43 west at UT-44 junction to Dutch John and Vernal, in Manilla.
